last_episode_to_air.name: And the Winner Is ...
last_episode_to_air.overview: On the final night of the competition, the best street racers in the world battle to be crowned Fastest in America. Memphis has the lead, but if Dream Team, Nola or Cali dig deep, they can still come from behind and take home the win.

name: Street Outlaws: Fastest In America
overview: Twelve of the fastest racing teams in America descend upon a secret concrete road in Wyoming to fight for the prestigious title of the Fastest Street Racer in America. Street Outlaws: Fastest in America returns October 19 at 8p on Discovery.

seasons.name: Street Outlaws: Fastest in America
seasons.overview: Season 1 - Twelve of the fastest racing teams in America descend upon a secret concrete road in Wyoming to fight for the prestigious title of the Fastest Street Racer in America. Street Outlaws: Fastest in America returns October 19 at 8p on Discovery.

seasons.name: Street Outlaws: Fastest in America
seasons.overview: Season 2 - Twelve of the fastest racing teams in America descend upon a secret concrete road in Wyoming to fight for the prestigious title of the Fastest Street Racer in America. Street Outlaws: Fastest in America returns October 19 at 8p on Discovery.

seasons.name: Street Outlaws: Fastest in America
seasons.overview: JJ da Boss kicks off another Fastest in America with eight teams and a purse of $100,000. But new rules make this contest unlike any other.

episodes.name: Biggest Street Race Ever
episodes.overview: JJ Da Boss has invited street racing teams to Memphis for a chance to win.

episodes.name: David Meet Goliath
episodes.overview: The heat is on as the South Carolina underdogs bring the fight to the St. Louis crew. It's all on display as mouthy leadership, fired-up tempers, and high pressure situations dominate a tension-filled night.

episodes.name: We Got Bad Blood
episodes.overview: The second matchup gets heated fast as Kye Kelley and his NOLA racers take on Birdman and his team from Texas.

episodes.name: First-Round Knockout
episodes.overview: The war continues between Team NOLA and Texas in a matchup that comes down to who can race best under pressure.

episodes.name: Civil War
episodes.overview: The North takes on the South in Memphis as Quinn and his family of Kentucky racers face off against Chris Rankin's ragtag team from the Northeast.

episodes.name: The Storm Rages On
episodes.overview: A storm is brewing as the fight between Kentucky and the Northeast continues.

episodes.name: Spinning Ain't Winning
episodes.overview: Chucky brings his infamous team from Detroit to take on Richard McCarver and his team of relatively unknown racers from Mississippi.

episodes.name: Move Over Motor City
episodes.overview: The final match rages on between the racers from Mississippi and the big-mouth, bigger-horsepower racers from Detroit.

episodes.name: The Final Four
episodes.overview: Chris Rankin's street-smart crew from the Northeast takes on the upstart Kye Kelley and his team from New Orleans in the second round of history's biggest street race.

episodes.name: The Take Down
episodes.overview: Rankin's Northeast crew refuses to be counted out as they attempt to outrun and outgun Kye and the NOLA crew.

episodes.name: Big, Bad Block
episodes.overview: The second match of round two pits Chucky and his team from Detroit against Chris Block and his South Carolina racers.

episodes.name: Too Much Power
episodes.overview: The fast-paced feud between Detroit and South Carolina continues and Motor City brings more power than their cars can handle.

episodes.name: NOLA vs. Detroit: Battle of the Heavyweights
episodes.overview: After weeks of racing, only Detroit and NOLA remain fighting for a chance to race Memphis for $100,000.

episodes.name: NOLA vs. Detroit: Dominate or Go Home
episodes.overview: Chucky Davis tries to dominate the night, while Kye Kelley makes a risky decision that could send his team home.

episodes.name: Memphis Vs. NOLA: 100 Grand Stand
episodes.overview: Memphis vs. NOLA: The final matchup is set, with $100,000 at stake. Kye Kelley's NOLA team is riding high after defeating Detroit, but JJ and the MSO think their team is unstoppable.

episodes.name: Memphis Vs. NOLA: Winner Takes All
episodes.overview: After an MSO runs off the road, the teams head into Round 2 knowing any mistake can be deadly. JJ and Kye Kelley fight to win the ultimate prize - $100,000 and the title of Fastest in America.

episodes.name: Aftermath
episodes.overview: Following the biggest street race in history that saw JJ Da Boss and his ruthless team from Memphis Street Outlaws down teams from all corners of the nation.

1.name: Street Outlaws: Fastest in America
1.overview: Season 1 - Twelve of the fastest racing teams in America descend upon a secret concrete road in Wyoming to fight for the prestigious title of the Fastest Street Racer in America. Street Outlaws: Fastest in America returns October 19 at 8p on Discovery.

episodes.name: Black Sheep vs Virginia Pt 1
episodes.overview: Fastest in America is back and bigger than ever, and the season kicks off with the first matchup in the Wildcard Round, where two new teams -- Black Sheep Mafia and Team Virginia -- battle it out to see who will get a spot in the final eight.

episodes.name: Black Sheep vs Virginia Pt 2
episodes.overview: The neck-and-neck Wildcard round between Black Sheep Mafia and Team Virginia continues! Axman stops up for his team in a big way while racers of Black Sheep Mafia show they can hold their own -- even separate from Team NOLA.

episodes.name: Black Sheep vs Virginia Grudge Night
episodes.overview: With so many big-time racers in town, everyone is staying on the streets for some high-stakes grudge racing. Racers compete for money to learn about the road while racers from Cali and North Carolina set up grudge race with a $10,000 pot.

episodes.name: Texas Vs Cali Part 1
episodes.overview: Teams Texas and California face off in the second matchup of the Wildcard Round and neither are pulling any punches! Texas wants to prove their early loss last season was a fluke while Caliâ€™s fresh faces are dead-set on making a big first impression.

episodes.name: Texas Vs Cali Part 2
episodes.overview: As the matchup between Texas and Cali continues, Birdman, Murillo and Team Texas look stronger than ever; however, Boddie and his racers from Cali won't be counted out, and if anyone can lead a team back from behind, it's racing legend Boddie.

episodes.name: Texas vs. Cali Grudge Night
episodes.overview: Another night of grudge racing hits the streets, and the drama continues between Kentucky and Texas when their racers can't lock in a race; then things get out of control when too many people try to get involved with a big money bet.

episodes.name: Kentucky vs. Wyoming Pt. 1
episodes.overview: Teams Kentucky and Wyoming prepare to face off in the third matchup of the wildcard round; although Kentucky appears to be the underdog, they refuse to lay down for anyone and will use any and every strategy to get an edge over the competition.

episodes.name: Kentucky vs. Wyoming Pt. 2
episodes.overview: The battle between Kentucky and Wyoming continues; while Sherrybeth and her team show they'll do whatever it takes, Wyoming holds their own; a fight to the finish looms as only one of the teams can make it into Round 1.

episodes.name: Kentucky vs. Wyoming Grudge Night
episodes.overview: The racers stick around to set up a fresh batch of grudge races; Kye Kelley struggles to get his tune right on a new road, while Fabian from Texas reminds all the racers of what they put on the line every time they climb into their cars.

episodes.name: Iowa Vs Utah Part 1
episodes.overview: Teams Utah and Iowa face off in the final matchup of the Wildcard Round. Utah's inexperience makes them seem like the underdogs, but after a few races -- and with $20,000 in their sights -- they quickly prove they're a force to be reckoned with.

episodes.name: Iowa Vs Utah Part 2
episodes.overview: The matchup between Utah and Iowa continues and things are all tied up going into the second round. Both teams' leaders scramble to rally their troops and come up with a winning strategy that can push them past the Wildcard Round and into Round 1.

episodes.name: Iowa vs Utah Grudge Night
episodes.overview: After the final Wildcard matchup, racers from all competing teams hit the streets for some grudge racing; Brian Davis and his Detroit racers prep their cars for a big-money matchup against Chris Rankin and his team from the Northeast.

episodes.name: Northeast vs Detroit (1)
episodes.overview: Teams from Detroit and the Northeast go head-to-head in the first matchup of Round 1; Rankin has a new group from the Northeast while Chucky Davis and his Detroit legends have an extra year of knowledge under their belt and are poised to win it all.

episodes.name: NE vs Detroit (2)
episodes.overview: The matchup between Detroit and the Northeast rages on and it's obvious this isn't going to be an easy win for either; Rankin and Chucky are ready to bring home a win for their teams but in this battle, it's going to come down to the very last race.

episodes.name: NE vs Detroit Grudge Night
episodes.overview: The racers stick around to lock in grudge races for money and for data on the road. Kentucky does what they can to prep for their matchup with Texas whilst NOLA struggles to get their rides in tune so they can stay in the competition.

episodes.name: Texas vs Kentucky (1)
episodes.overview: Teams Texas and Wyoming have been gunning for each other ever since Varni and Sherrybeth clashed in Wyoming; they finally get their chance to battle and both teams are ready to pull out all the stops to make it to the next round.

episodes.name: Texas vs Kentucky (2)
episodes.overview: The battle between Texas and Kentucky continues; while Kentucky may be down, they're ready to give it all they've got to win; Texas focuses on keeping the lead; Team Kentucky has a few extra tricks up their sleeve that could turn things around.

episodes.name: Texas vs Kentucky Grudge Night
episodes.overview: The infamous Lizzy Musi is back on the streets looking to line up some grudge racing in her car.

episodes.name: Black Sheep vs SC (1)
episodes.overview: Chris Block and his new South Carolina team hit the streets to face off with Brent Self and his new team called the Black Sheep Mafia; Block's team has a whole new attitude, but the Black Sheep are strong in every way and are ready to put up a fight.

episodes.name: Black Sheep vs South Carolina (2)
episodes.overview: The fight between South Carolina and the Black Sheep Mafia rages on; Chris Block's team suffers a surprise loss when a racer decides to quit the team; the Black Sheep are poised to show off what a truly unified team can do.

episodes.name: Black Sheep vs South Carolina Grudge Night
episodes.overview: After quitting team South Carolina, Boogie gets a call from his ex-teammates to settle the score with Chris Block in a night of grudge racing; racers from NOLA and Iowa prepare for their upcoming matchup.

episodes.name: Nola vs Iowa, Part 1
episodes.overview: Fastest in America is back and badder than ever! The list of players is already stacked but things get even more interesting as eight new teams battle it out in a series of Wildcard Rounds to see who will join the final eight vying for a shot at Memphis.

episodes.name: NOLA vs Iowa Pt 2
episodes.overview: The list of players is already stacked but things get even more interesting as eight new teams battle it out in a series of Wildcard Rounds.

episodes.name: NOLA vs Iowa Grudge Night
episodes.overview: Fastest in America is back and badder than ever! The list of players is already stacked but things get even more interesting as eight new teams battle it out in a series of Wildcard Rounds to see who will join the final eight vying for a shot at Memphis.

episodes.name: Texas vs Black Sheep, Part 1
episodes.overview: A windy and dusty night on the streets of Wyoming creates challenging racing conditions for powerhouse teams Texas and Black Sheep Mafia; with $20,000 up for grabs, one veteran racer pushes the limits of the road too far.

episodes.name: Texas vs Black Sheep Pt 2
episodes.overview: Texas and Black Sheep Mafia continue their Round Two battle; after a devastating crash, Texas must regroup and try to win for their missing team leader; Black Sheep Mafia isn't letting up, but the dusty road takes another racer down.

episodes.name: Texas vs Black Sheep Grudge Night
episodes.overview: The racers are on the street for another night of grudge racing.

episodes.name: NE vs NOLA Pt 1
episodes.overview: Kye Kelley's Team NOLA and Chris Rankin's Team Northeast go head to head in the second match-up of round two to see who will face Black Sheep Mafia; NOLA has been making big passes all season, but the Northeast is ready to come out swinging.

episodes.name: NE vs NOLA Pt 2
episodes.overview: The matchup between Team Northeast and NOLA continues; Northeast team leader Chris Rankin is frustrated with his team's performance and is determined to not let his team fall apart like it did last year.

episodes.name: NE vs. NOLA Grudge Night
episodes.overview: Black Sheep Mafia and NOLA tune up for their final grudge-racing matchup.

episodes.name: NOLA vs. Black Sheep Pt 1
episodes.overview: Brent Self is ready to prove himself as Black Sheep Mafia takes on his former team NOLA; Black Sheep Mafia hope to demonstrate their strengths while Team NOLA is looking for a win and a shot at redemption against Memphis.

episodes.name: NOLA vs. Black Sheep Pt 2
episodes.overview: The battle between Black Sheep Mafia and Team NOLA rages on. The battle between former teammates continues as Black Sheep Mafia and Team NOLA fight to see who will get a shot at the MSO.

episodes.name: NOLA vs. Black Sheep Grudge Night
episodes.overview: With the rematch between Memphis and NOLA set for next week, both teams hit the streets for a final chance at data. NOLA has been on the street for weeks so Memphis will have to rely on their street sense to make it down the concrete road

episodes.name: Memphis vs. NOLA, Part 1
episodes.overview: The Memphis Street Outlaws are back and prepared to battle Team NOLA in the final matchup of the season; JJ and the MSO are fresh in the competition; NOLA is hungry and have the horsepower to pull off an upset.

episodes.name: Memphis vs. NOLA, Part 2
episodes.overview: The streets are still hot and the battle continues to rage between Memphis and NOLA; Memphis may be out-powered and outgunned but NOLA must remain on their toes if they want to stay ahead and come out with a win.

episodes.name: To The Finish Line
episodes.overview: Revisiting every runway, every tight race and every crash; a sneak peek at the upcoming season of "Street Outlaws" back in Oklahoma City.

2.name: Street Outlaws: Fastest in America
2.overview: Season 2 - Twelve of the fastest racing teams in America descend upon a secret concrete road in Wyoming to fight for the prestigious title of the Fastest Street Racer in America. Street Outlaws: Fastest in America returns October 19 at 8p on Discovery.

episodes.name: The Captain's Race
episodes.overview: Eight team captains race off to determine first round matchups for Fastest in America. Kye Kelley and team NOLA take advantage of a rule violation and Team Cali fakes a break to manipulate who they will race first.

episodes.name: Memphis vs. Texas
episodes.overview: Team Texas is Memphis' first big challenge of the year. Murillo and Birdman bring their biggest hitters to the party but Memphis is determined to show their grit.

episodes.name: Notheast vs. Southern Assassins
episodes.overview: Rankin claims that the Northeast is stronger than ever, but they've got a challenge going up against the Southern Assassins. Even when everything that can goes wrong Jim rallies his team to stick together and give Northeast serious competition.

episodes.name: Cali vs. Detroit
episodes.overview: Boddie leads Team Cali in a matchup against Brian Davisâ€™s Team Detroit. Although Cali chose to race Detroit, it turns into the hardest fought showdown of the season. Between crashes, fights, and drama, whoever wins this one will have to truly earn it.

episodes.name: NOLA vs. the Misfits
episodes.overview: Experienced Team NOLA goes up against Ricky Wilson's new team, the Misfits. And even though NOLA has been to the finals of Fastest in America twice, the Misfits put them back on their heels, and NOLA is in for a serious fight.

episodes.name: Cali vs. NOLA
episodes.overview: Boddie's Team Cali goes up against Kye Kelley and Team NOLA in a knock-down, drag-out fight to make it to the finals of Fastest in America. NOLA might be the favorites going in, but Cali isn't gonna quit even when the sun comes up.

episodes.name: Memphis vs. Northeast
episodes.overview: In the last matchup before the finals, Memphis takes on Team Northeast to prove that they can make it from the beginning. But Relic is a detail-oriented leader and the Northeast's big mouths and big money bets make for contentious competition.

episodes.name: Memphis vs. Cali
episodes.overview: Memphis faces Team Cali in the final showdown for $100K and the title of Fastest in America. But when pressure busts a pipe and some racers disagree with Boddie's decisions, Cali begins to waver and the MSO looks for an advantage.

3.name: Street Outlaws: Fastest in America
3.overview: JJ da Boss kicks off another Fastest in America with eight teams and a purse of $100,000. But new rules make this contest unlike any other.

episodes.name: Gamechanger
episodes.overview: The title of Fastest in America is up for grabs with new teams, new cars and new rules. Tonight, the eight captains will each choose two drivers to compete in a 16-car bracket. The goal: go fast, stack cash and be the last driver standing.

episodes.name: Small Tires, Big Mouths
episodes.overview: On Night Two, drivers compete on small tires, but when Cali Nate pushes limits, tempers flare and drivers call foul.

episodes.name: Cali Nate's Secret Weapon
episodes.overview: The Dream Team has an early lead and the other captains must close the gap or run the risk of getting left behind. But little do they know, Cali Nate has a secret weapon up his sleeve.

episodes.name: Kye Gets His Groove Back
episodes.overview: After several nights of struggle, Kye Kelley and his team from NOLA make big gains on the street.

episodes.name: Tricia's Back
episodes.overview: On night five, Tricia makes her return to racing after her horrible crash and JJ Da Boss tries a power move to get the MSO back to the top. But Cali, Nola and the Dream Team aren't rolling over easily.

episodes.name: Throwing Shade and Punches
episodes.overview: On the final night of the low-money rounds, tensions boil over between Sherrybeth and Brett, while Cali and Detroit end up in an all-out brawl.

episodes.name: Double the Money
episodes.overview: It's race night seven, and the cash up for grabs has doubled; with this much money on the line, there's a lot to lose, and it's anyone's game to win.

episodes.name: 10K Grudge Race
episodes.overview: With only two race nights left, Kye Kelley and his team from NOLA are still in third place, but when Kye calls out Cali Nate for a huge 10K grudge race, it throws the entire competition into chaos.

episodes.name: And the Winner Is ...
episodes.overview: On the final night of the competition, the best street racers in the world battle to be crowned Fastest in America. Memphis has the lead, but if Dream Team, Nola or Cali dig deep, they can still come from behind and take home the win.
